Members of the “Camerata” from what is today this country included the 
composer of the opera Dafne. Another composer from this modern country wrote in a 
highly chromatic style after murdering his wife and her lover. A girls’ orphanage (*) 
in this modern country is where a man nicknamed the “Red Priest” worked when 
composing The Contest Between Harmony and Invention. In 1607, a composer from 
what is now this country composed the earliest opera that is still regularly 
performed, (*) L’Orfeo. For the point, name this home country of the composers Vivaldi and 
Monteverdi.=====
Republic of Italy =====